SUMMARIZER="J">

Exactly 47 years after Leonard Bernstein debuted as conductor of New York 
Philharmonic, the orchestra remembered the maestro at a concert that included selections 
from his "Mass," "Chichester Psalms," and "Candide." Mr. Bernstein died on October 
16th.

Family members and friends of the world renown conductor introduced various 
selections. An international roster of musicians and singers joined the orchestra as guest 
artists.

Conductors were Michael Tillson Thomas, Michael Barrett, Christoph Eschenbach and 
James Levine. The orchestra played the overture to "Candide" with a symbolically empty 
podium, which brought tears to some of the invited audience and a standing ovation.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d072"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="LA121490-0148"
